This article is an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on December 19, 2014. The order adjusts certain rates of pay for various positions and roles within the United States government. It includes adjustments to the rates of basic pay for statutory pay systems, senior executives in the Senior Executive Service, certain executive, legislative, and judicial salaries, members of the uniformed services, and administrative law judges. The order also establishes locality-based comparability payments and sets effective dates for the changes. This executive order supersedes a previous order issued in December 2013.